Since Ashley has a total of $17.25, it must be the case that the sum of these values is 17.25: 0.25q+0.50(q+9)=17.25 We can now solve for q:
\begin{aligned} 0.25q+0.50(q+9) \amp= 17.25 \\ 0.25q+0.50q+4.50 \amp= 17.25 \\ 0.75q+4.50 \amp= 17.25 \\ 0.75q \amp= 12.75 \\ q \amp= 17 \end{aligned}
Ashley has 17 quarters, andtherefore 26 fifty-cent pieces.

The domain is the set of first components of a relation; for this relation, the first components are
        \{4, \ 2, \ 3, \ 0\}
    The range is the set of the second components, which are
        \{6, \ 5, \ 0\}
    Notice that 6 was a second component twice. This is allowed, but we only need to list it in the range once.

